@startuml digital_key_and_drive_state_to_smk_auth_gate_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Digital Key And Drive State To SMK Auth Gate Signal Flow\n(digital-key access + drive state -> SMK key-auth and immobilizer gate)

participant "Digital-key bus" as DKey #F4F7FB
participant "Vehicle state bus" as Veh #E8F0FE
participant "SMK\nsmart-key owner" as SMK #E8F7E8
participant "Immobilizer state bus" as ImmoBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\naccess readers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== SMK Inputs ==

DKey -> SMK : frmDigitalKeyStateMsg\nVehicleAccessState / KeyPresence
Veh -> SMK : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\ngDriveState
activate SMK
SMK -> SMK : dkeyInputStale / vehicleInputStale\nlease checks
SMK -> SMK : if vehicle stale then\ndriveState = 3
SMK -> SMK : accessAuthorized =\ndkey fresh and KeyPresence == 1\nand VehicleAccessState >= 1
SMK -> SMK : immobilizerState = 1 by default,\n0 when vehicle input fresh and driveState > 0
SMK -> SMK : keyAuthState = accessAuthorized
note right of SMK
Representative gating inputs
- VehicleAccessState
- KeyPresence
- gDriveState
end note

== SMK Publish ==

SMK -> ImmoBus : frmImmobilizerStateMsg\nImmobilizerState / KeyAuthState
note right of SMK
Representative outputs
- ImmobilizerState
- KeyAuthState
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

ImmoBus -> Obs : immobilizer/auth visibility /\ndoor and access observers
deactivate SMK

note over DKey, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Digital-key state and drive state reach SMK
2. SMK applies freshness and parked/drive gating
3. SMK derives key-auth and immobilizer posture
4. SMK publishes immobilizer and auth state for downstream readers
end note

@enduml
